Hundreds of staff at the National Financial Aid Scheme are expected to strike on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Hundreds of staff at the National Financial Aid Scheme are expected to strike on Monday. They are upset about non-payment of bonuses, and allege victimisation. READ: NSFAS stops SMS communication Negotiations between the workers and management have failed. Staff affiliated to Nehawu will hand over a memorandum to Higher Education Minister, Blade Nzimande. Management says the strike will not hamper students applying for loans for next year.